# Summary as Default Landing Page

**Rule:** Users must always land on the **Summary** page first, never Meeting Prep or any other view.

## Implementation

- **`src/config/navigation.js`**: `roleDefaults.bm` must be `"bm-dashboard"` (Summary). Do not change to `"bm-meeting-prep"` or any other view.
- **`src/components/interactive/InteractiveDashboard.jsx`**: 
  - The Summary (dashboard) section must be the **first** section in the BM page layout (top of scroll).
  - `firstViewId` / initial scroll highlight must use `roleDefaults[role]` (or `"bm-dashboard"` for BM), never hardcode `"bm-meeting-prep"`.
- **`src/context/AppContext.jsx`**: Uses `roleDefaults` for initial view—keep as-is.

## Do Not

- Set Meeting Prep as the default landing view.
- Put Meeting Prep above Summary in the BM dashboard scroll order.
- Hardcode `"bm-meeting-prep"` as the initial/first view.
